<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-08-03T10:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-08-03T10:00:00-05:00" n="850" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d850">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">810.5051/7–2744: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the Ambassador in Colombia</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Lane</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-08-03T11:00:00-04:00">August 3,
                                    1944—11 a.m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>956. Address note to Foreign Minister in Uricoechea case, subject of your
                            no. 1320, July 27.<note n="62" xml:id="d850fn62">Not printed.</note> Ask
                            that he inform the court that immunity should be granted to Rubber
                            Development Corporation, since it is owned and controlled by the
                            Government of the United States, and carries on its activities in
                            Colombia as an agency of this Government, acting under its
                            direction.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Stettinius</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>